verbose_text: When we analyzed men and women separately, the risks of CVD, IHD, and ischemic stroke were increased significantly above the FSG levels of 110, 100, and 126 mg/dL, respectively, in men (XREF_FIG and Supplementary Table 2), and 120, 126, and 120 mg/dL, respectively, in women (XREF_FIG and Supplementary Table 3) after additional adjustment for menopause status.
